## Important changes from your current CSS

Remove these existing mascot rules:

```css
width: clamp(420px, 46vw, 590px);
right: clamp(-40px, 4vw, 60px);
bottom: clamp(-180px, -12vw, -80px);
```

They cause the mascot to move unpredictably when the viewport width changes.

The new version anchors it consistently using:

```css
left: 50%;
bottom: -6%;
transform: translateX(-50%) scaleX(-1);
```

Also change your current error title:

```css
font-weight: 800;
```

to:

```css
font-family: 'Ubuntu', Arial, sans-serif;
font-weight: 700;
```

because the design calls for **Ubuntu Bold**, not an artificial weight of `800`.

